%N A396338 Decimal expansion of phi*G, where phi = (1+sqrt(5))/2 is the golden ratio and G is Catalan's constant.
%C A396338 It is not known whether this constant is irrational or transcendental.
%F A396338 Equals A001622 * A006752.
%e A396338 1.48206346390423314188438200268250263660035921348181344...
%t A396338 RealDigits[GoldenRatio*Catalan, 10, 105][[1]]
%o A396338 (PARI) default(realprecision, 50); (1+sqrt(5))/2*Catalan
%o A396338 (Python) from mpmath import mp, phi, catalan; mp.dps=50; print(phi*catalan)
